        @PostMapping(value="/postDataUpload")
public java.lang.String handlePostFileUpload(@RequestParam(value="file")

                                                                                   org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.support.RedirectAttributes redirectAttributes)
        Handles file uploads, for reading in the big Tumblr XML Export. Actual logic is handled by the BlogXmlReader class; this method simply calls that class, and then (upon success) redirects to the index.

        redirectAttributes - not used
        Returns:

      • showViewer

        @RequestMapping(value="/postViewer",
                method=GET)
public java.lang.String showViewer(@RequestParam(value="id")
                                                                                                    java.lang.Long postID,
                                                                                                    org.springframework.ui.Model model)
        This request is used to populate the viewer. It first determines the correct viewer to show (Regular, Photo, etc.), then returns the correct template to show that type of post. In this case, the pages are being populated by Thymeleaf, rather than jQuery, so the Model is populated with the necessary data.
        Parameters:
        postID - The ID of the post to be viewed (regardless of type)
        model - The model to be populated with post data, for use by Thymeleaf in the HTML template
        Returns:
        The name of the template to use for rendering the output
